{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892127986,"sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","part":{"id":"prt_d7b690e58001m6Jm6nw1NB30x8","messageID":"msg_d7b68c9450010fgvvgZtrZSyzu","sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: CLI Invoke/Status Commands (AR-023)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nProvide the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to agent endpoints, while the `status` command retrieves deployment status from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - CLI options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke` without any options\n- **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n  - `header_list` = `None`\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path override\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n\n#### Scenario: Payload specification\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"input\": \"test\"}'`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL parse the payload as JSON and include it in the HTTP POST request\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple header options\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\" --header \"X-Custom: value\"`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL include both headers in the HTTP request\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with AgentCube provider to invoke via AgentRuntime CR endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with K8s provider for direct HTTP invocation to the NodePort Service\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - payload and header validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate the payload and headers before sending the request.\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload 'invalid json'`\n- **WHEN** the CLI attempts to parse the payload\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message in red indicating invalid JSON\n- **AND** exit with code `1` before invoking the runtime\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid header format (missing colon)\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"InvalidHeaderWithoutColon\"`\n- **WHEN** the CLI parses the header\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating expected `key:value` format\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Valid payload parsing\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'`\n- **WHEN** the payload is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL successfully convert it to a Python dictionary\n- **AND** pass it to `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`\n\n#### Scenario: Header parsing with colon in value\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer: token:with:colons\"`\n- **WHEN** the header is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL split only on the first colon\n- **AND** produce header key `Authorization` with value `Bearer: token:with:colons`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - workspace metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to invoke.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` file\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Agent not published\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but has no `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the agent must be published first\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - HTTP invocation\n\nThe system SHALL POST JSON payloads to the agent endpoint with appropriate headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Direct HTTP invocation to K8s NodePort\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and metadata contains `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n- **AND** the payload is valid JSON\n- **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `{service_url}` with JSON body\n- **AND** include custom headers if provided\n- **AND** return the response JSON\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube CR invocation via Router\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and metadata contains `router_url` and `agent_id`\n- **AND** `k8s_deployment.type` is `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n- **WHEN** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL POST to `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- **AND** include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` if `session_id` exists in metadata\n- **AND** include `Content-Type: application/json` header\n- **AND** return the response\n\n#### Scenario: Session header from metadata\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id = \"abc-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n- **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc-123`\n\n#### Scenario: Successful invocation response\n- **GIVEN** the HTTP request succeeds with status 200\n- **AND** the response contains valid JSON `{\"result\": \"success\"}`\n- **WHEN** the response is received\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display the response in a formatted manner\n- **AND** exit with code `0`\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP error response\n- **GIVEN** the HTTP request returns status 4xx or 5xx\n- **WHEN** the response is processed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception\n- **AND** the CLI SHALL print the error and exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully using the `_handle_error` pattern.\n\n#### Scenario: Error with verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during invoke and `--verbose` is enabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error invoking agent: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Print the full traceback\n  3. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: Error without verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during invoke and `--verbose` is disabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error invoking agent: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)` without printing traceback\n\n#### Scenario: Network timeout\n- **GIVEN** the agent endpoint is unreachable or times out\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the timeout/connection error\n- **AND** raise a user-friendly error message\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - CLI options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `status` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube status` without any options\n- **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path override\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with AgentCube provider to check AgentRuntime CR status\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the status command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use `StatusRuntime` with K8s provider to check Deployment status\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - workspace metadata validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to check status.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n- **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no metadata file\n- **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Agent not published\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but has no `agent_id`\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_published\", \"message\": \"Agent has not been published\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - status retrieval\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve and display agent status from the appropriate provider.\n\n#### Scenario: K8s provider - Deployment status\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and Kubernetes client initializes successfully\n- **AND** metadata contains `k8s_deployment.name` and `k8s_deployment.namespace`\n- **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(agent_name)`\n- **AND** return status including:\n  - `status`: `\"running\"`, `\"pending\"`, `\"failed\"`, or `\"not_found\"`\n  - `deployment_name`: name of the Deployment\n  - `namespace`: deployment namespace\n  - `replicas`: number of desired replicas\n  - `ready_replicas`: number of ready replicas\n  - `service_url`: the NodePort service URL if available\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider - CR status\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and the CR exists in Kubernetes\n- **AND** metadata contains `agent_id` and `k8s_deployment.name`\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL query the AgentRuntime CR\n- **AND** read status from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present\n- **AND** return `status`, `agentEndpoint`, and other CR status fields\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube CR - status present\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists with `.status.status = \"Ready\"`\n- **AND** `.status.agentEndpoint = \"http://router/v1/...\"`\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` processes the CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"Ready\", \"agentEndpoint\": \"http://router/v1/...\", ...}`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube CR - no status field\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `.status` field\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` processes the CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\", \"message\": \"CR exists but status not yet populated\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube CR - not found\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist in the namespace\n- **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` attempts to get the CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\", \"message\": \"AgentRuntime CR not found\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - output formatting\n\nThe system SHALL display status information in a Rich `Table` format.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful status display\n- **GIVEN** the status is successfully retrieved\n- **WHEN** the CLI displays the result\n- **THEN** the system SHALL render a Rich `Table` with:\n  - Property column (e.g., \"Status\", \"Agent ID\", \"Endpoint\", \"Replicas\")\n  - Value column with appropriate styling\n\n#### Scenario: Running status styling\n- **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"running\"` or `\"Ready\"`\n- **WHEN** displayed in the table\n- **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in green\n\n#### Scenario: Pending status styling\n- **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"pending\"` or `\"created_no_status\"`\n- **WHEN** displayed in the table\n- **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in yellow\n\n#### Scenario: Failed/error status styling\n- **GIVEN** the agent status is `\"failed\"`, `\"error\"`, or `\"not_found\"`\n- **WHEN** displayed in the table\n- **THEN** the status value SHALL be styled in red\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - exit codes\n\nThe system SHALL exit with appropriate codes based on status.\n\n#### Scenario: Status is not_published\n- **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n- **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n- **THEN** the system SHALL print guidance to publish first\n- **AND** exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Status is error or not_found\n- **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status` in `[\"error\", \"failed\", \"not_found\", \"not_found_in_k8s\"]`\n- **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n- **THEN** the system SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Status is running or ready\n- **GIVEN** `get_status` returns `status` in `[\"running\", \"Ready\", \"ready\"]`\n- **WHEN** the CLI processes the result\n- **THEN** the system SHALL exit with code `0`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Status command - error handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle errors gracefully using the `_handle_error` pattern.\n\n#### Scenario: Error with verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during status check and `--verbose` is enabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error checking agent status: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Print the full traceback\n  3. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: Error without verbose mode\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during status check and `--verbose` is disabled\n- **WHEN** the error is caught in the CLI command\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  1. Print \"Error checking agent status: {error message}\" in red\n  2. Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)` without printing traceback\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes client initialization failure\n- **GIVEN** the Kubernetes client fails to initialize (e.g., no kubeconfig, invalid credentials)\n- **WHEN** `KubernetesProvider` or `AgentCubeProvider` is instantiated in `StatusRuntime`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an appropriate exception that is propagated through `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke` and `status` command definitions |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` class with invocation logic |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` class with status retrieval logic |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` for K8s status queries |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` for CR status queries |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for loading agent metadata |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation for metadata |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML parsing for metadata files |\n| `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for agent invocation |\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | Kubernetes client for CR queries (optional) |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich text output and table formatting |\n\n---\n\n## CLI Usage Examples\n\n```bash\n# Invoke agent with default empty payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent\n\n# Invoke agent with custom payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --payload '{\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"}'\n\n# Invoke agent with custom headers\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}' \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" \\\n  --header \"X-Request-ID: abc-123\"\n\n# Invoke agent on Kubernetes provider\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --payload '{\"data\": [1,2,3]}'\n\n# Check agent status\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent\n\n# Check status for Kubernetes deployment\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --provider k8s\n\n# Check status with verbose output\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --verbose\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | Reads metadata created during publish phase |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | Queries Deployment and Service status |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Queries AgentRuntime CR status |\n| `MetadataService` | Loads agent metadata for endpoint discovery |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | Makes HTTP requests to agent endpoints |\n| `StatusRuntime` | Aggregates status from various providers |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `invoke` command requires a published agent with valid `agent_endpoint` (for K8s) or `router_url` (for AgentCube)\n- For `provider=agentcube`, the metadata must include `router_url` to construct the invocation URL\n- For `provider=k8s`, the metadata must include `k8s_deployment.service_url` or derive it from `node_port`\n- The `status` command reads from `k8s_deployment` metadata populated by the `publish` command\n- Both commands use the `_handle_error` pattern consistent with other CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`)\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775892127977,"end":1775892127984}}}}
