{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892137107,"sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6b7f8b001Y4zBMCCHqzRIJS","messageID":"msg_d7b6b76460017TeeebMqYZnoWO","sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: This document describes the delta specification for implementing the `invoke` and `status` commands in the AgentCube CLI.\n5: \n6: ## Current State\n7: - The CLI framework exists with command structure\n8: - Basic commands like `init`, `build`, `pack`, `publish` are available\n9: - No execution management commands exist yet\n10: - Backend API for execution management exists (assumed)\n11: \n12: ## Target State\n13: Fully functional `invoke` and `status` commands that:\n14: - Allow users to trigger agent executions with custom inputs\n15: - Enable monitoring of execution status\n16: - Provide clear output formatting\n17: - Support both synchronous and asynchronous workflows\n18: \n19: ## Delta Analysis\n20: \n21: ### New Components\n22: \n23: 1. **Invoke Command Module** (`cmd/cli/invoke.py`)\n24:    - CLI interface for invoke command\n25:    - Input parameter parsing (JSON file, key-value pairs)\n26:    - Execution request construction\n27:    - Immediate response handling with execution ID\n28: \n29: 2. **Status Command Module** (`cmd/cli/status.py`)\n30:    - CLI interface for status command\n31:    - Execution ID validation\n32:    - Status polling logic\n33:    - Result display formatting\n34: \n35: 3. **Execution Client** (`cmd/cli/internal/execution.py`)\n36:    - HTTP client for execution API\n37:    - Request/response handling\n38:    - Error code mapping\n39: \n40: 4. **Output Formatter** (`cmd/cli/internal/formatter.py`)\n41:    - JSON output formatting\n42:    - Table output formatting\n43:    - Color coding for status states\n44: \n45: ### Modified Components\n46: - `cmd/cli/main.py` - Add invoke and status subcommands\n47: \n48: ### Dependencies\n49: - Requires existing CLI framework\n50: - Requires backend execution API availability\n51: - May leverage existing auth module from AR-022\n52: \n53: ## Interface Specification\n54: \n55: ### Invoke Command\n56: \n57: #### Command Signature\n58: ```bash\n59: agentcube invoke [OPTIONS] <agent-name-or-id>\n60: ```\n61: \n62: #### Options\n63: - `--input, -i`: Input parameters as JSON string or file path\n64: - `--input-file, -f`: Path to JSON file containing inputs\n65: - `--async`: Return immediately with execution ID (default: true)\n66: - `--sync, -s`: Wait for execution to complete\n67: - `--timeout`: Timeout for sync mode in seconds (default: 300)\n68: - `--output, -o`: Output format (json, table, yaml)\n69: - `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n70: \n71: #### Exit Codes\n72: - `0`: Success (execution completed or submitted)\n73: - `1`: General error\n74: - `2`: Agent not found\n75: - `3`: Invalid input parameters\n76: - `4`: Execution submission failed\n77: - `5`: Sync execution timeout\n78: \n79: ### Status Command\n80: \n81: #### Command Signature\n82: ```bash\n83: agentcube status [OPTIONS] <execution-id>\n84: ```\n85: \n86: #### Options\n87: - `--watch, -w`: Continuously poll for status updates\n88: - `--interval`: Polling interval in seconds (default: 5)\n89: - `--output, -o`: Output format (json, table, yaml)\n90: - `--verbose, -v`: Verbose output\n91: \n92: #### Exit Codes\n93: - `0`: Execution completed successfully\n94: - `1`: General error\n95: - `2`: Execution not found\n96: - `3`: Execution failed\n97: - `4`: Execution still running (when not in watch mode)\n98: \n99: ## Implementation Notes\n100: - Follow existing CLI patterns from other commands\n101: - Use shared HTTP client for API communication\n102: - Support both sync and async invocation modes\n103: - Implement proper polling backoff for status command\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the `invoke` and `status` commands in the AgentCube CLI.\n\n## Current State\n- The CLI framework exists with command structure\n- Basic commands like `init`, `build`, `pack`, `publish` are available\n- No execution management commands exist yet\n- Backend API for execution management exists (assumed)\n\n## Target State\nFully functional `invoke` and `status` commands that:\n- Allow users to trigger agent executions with custom inputs\n- Enable monitoring of execution status\n- Provide clear output formatting\n- Support both synchronous and asynchronous workflows\n\n## Delta Analysis\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892137086,"end":1775892137104}}}}
