{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892323171,"sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6e53fa0016426217sijqC6H","messageID":"msg_d7b6e35fd001GlT57v25MZLq7j","sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: CLI Invoke/Status Commands (AR-023)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-023  \n6: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n7: **Language:** Python  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Provide the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to agent endpoints, while the `status` command retrieves deployment status from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Invoke command - CLI options and defaults\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Default option values\n21: - **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube invoke` without any options\n22: - **WHEN** the command parses arguments\n23: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n24:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n25:   - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n26:   - `header_list` = `None`\n27:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`\n28:   - `verbose` = `False`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Workspace path override\n31: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `-f /path/to/agent` or `--workspace /path/to/agent`\n32: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided path\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Payload specification\n36: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"input\": \"test\"}'`\n37: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL parse the payload as JSON and include it in the HTTP POST request\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Multiple header options\n41: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\" --header \"X-Custom: value\"`\n42: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n43: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL include both headers in the HTTP request\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider selection - AgentCube\n46: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider agentcube`\n47: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with AgentCube provider to invoke via AgentRuntime CR endpoint\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Provider selection - Kubernetes\n51: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--provider k8s`\n52: - **WHEN** the invoke command executes\n53: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `InvokeRuntime` with K8s provider for direct HTTP invocation to the NodePort Service\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: Invoke command - payload and header validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate the payload and headers before sending the request.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Invalid JSON payload\n62: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload 'invalid json'`\n63: - **WHEN** the CLI attempts to parse the payload\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message in red indicating invalid JSON\n65: - **AND** exit with code `1` before invoking the runtime\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid header format (missing colon)\n68: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"InvalidHeaderWithoutColon\"`\n69: - **WHEN** the CLI parses the header\n70: - **THEN** the system SHALL print an error message indicating expected `key:value` format\n71: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Valid payload parsing\n74: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--payload '{\"message\": \"hello\", \"count\": 5}'`\n75: - **WHEN** the payload is parsed\n76: - **THEN** the system SHALL successfully convert it to a Python dictionary\n77: - **AND** pass it to `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Header parsing with colon in value\n80: - **GIVEN** the user specifies `--header \"Authorization: Bearer: token:with:colons\"`\n81: - **WHEN** the header is parsed\n82: - **THEN** the system SHALL split only on the first colon\n83: - **AND** produce header key `Authorization` with value `Bearer: token:with:colons`\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Requirement: Invoke command - workspace metadata validation\n88: \n89: The system SHALL validate workspace metadata before attempting to invoke.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Missing workspace directory\n92: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n93: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` is invoked\n94: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating the directory does not exist\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Missing agent_metadata.yaml\n97: - **GIVEN** the workspace exists but contains no `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` file\n98: - **WHEN** metadata loading is attempted\n99: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating the metadata file is missing\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 420. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: CLI Invoke/Status Commands (AR-023)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\nProvide the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to interact with deployed agents. The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to agent endpoints, while the `status` command retrieves deployment status from either AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command - CLI options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` command via Typer with specified options and sensible defaults.\n\n#### Scenario: Default option values","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775892323157,"end":1775892323168}}}}
