{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892334220,"sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6e7a73001UEnVRV8iFhEiZg","messageID":"msg_d7b6e5b91001UwzsFWIQ9c4PP2","sessionID":"ses_284984126ffeSNmBADjiRS4L0q","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"wc -l /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md && tail -50 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","description":"Check file completeness"},"output":"420 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md\n## CLI Usage Examples\n\n```bash\n# Invoke agent with default empty payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent\n\n# Invoke agent with custom payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --payload '{\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"}'\n\n# Invoke agent with custom headers\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}' \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" \\\n  --header \"X-Request-ID: abc-123\"\n\n# Invoke agent on Kubernetes provider\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --payload '{\"data\": [1,2,3]}'\n\n# Check agent status\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent\n\n# Check status for Kubernetes deployment\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --provider k8s\n\n# Check status with verbose output\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --verbose\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | Reads metadata created during publish phase |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | Queries Deployment and Service status |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Queries AgentRuntime CR status |\n| `MetadataService` | Loads agent metadata for endpoint discovery |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | Makes HTTP requests to agent endpoints |\n| `StatusRuntime` | Aggregates status from various providers |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `invoke` command requires a published agent with valid `agent_endpoint` (for K8s) or `router_url` (for AgentCube)\n- For `provider=agentcube`, the metadata must include `router_url` to construct the invocation URL\n- For `provider=k8s`, the metadata must include `k8s_deployment.service_url` or derive it from `node_port`\n- The `status` command reads from `k8s_deployment` metadata populated by the `publish` command\n- Both commands use the `_handle_error` pattern consistent with other CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`)\n","metadata":{"output":"420 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md\n## CLI Usage Examples\n\n```bash\n# Invoke agent with default empty payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent\n\n# Invoke agent with custom payload\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --payload '{\"input\": \"Hello, Agent!\"}'\n\n# Invoke agent with custom headers\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}' \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\" \\\n  --header \"X-Request-ID: abc-123\"\n\n# Invoke agent on Kubernetes provider\nagentcube invoke -f ./my-agent --provider k8s --payload '{\"data\": [1,2,3]}'\n\n# Check agent status\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent\n\n# Check status for Kubernetes deployment\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --provider k8s\n\n# Check status with verbose output\nagentcube status -f ./my-agent --verbose\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n| Component | Integration |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | Reads metadata created during publish phase |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | Queries Deployment and Service status |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Queries AgentRuntime CR status |\n| `MetadataService` | Loads agent metadata for endpoint discovery |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | Makes HTTP requests to agent endpoints |\n| `StatusRuntime` | Aggregates status from various providers |\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- The `invoke` command requires a published agent with valid `agent_endpoint` (for K8s) or `router_url` (for AgentCube)\n- For `provider=agentcube`, the metadata must include `router_url` to construct the invocation URL\n- For `provider=k8s`, the metadata must include `k8s_deployment.service_url` or derive it from `node_port`\n- The `status` command reads from `k8s_deployment` metadata populated by the `publish` command\n- Both commands use the `_handle_error` pattern consistent with other CLI commands (`pack`, `build`, `publish`)\n","exit":0,"description":"Check file completeness","truncated":false},"title":"Check file completeness","time":{"start":1775892334205,"end":1775892334218}}}}
